text:
reading about the r. kelly documentary and seeing that video of lil' wayne discussing being raped at the age of 11 had me reflecting on a conversation i had over the holidays and recalling times where i experienced grooming, sexual harassment, and sexual assault at the hands of influential mentors and supervisors (and other conversations i wish i'd never had). the situations i wrote about in my essay are only a splash in the ocean of sexually-related trauma that i have endured, witnessed, and been told about from others.
üñ§
i have let people down because i didn't know better. and i've kept in contact with predators because i didn't want to believe i was a victim. i've been silent due to shame. and i've been confused and distant.
üñ§
a quote that i've been repeating far too often is, "a body can only hold so much grief." i've been wanting to write about the joyful things in my life, but i'm finding myself more and more pulled to write about traumatic and "taboo" subjects. i trust that i am in a space to handle reliving these things.
üñ§
i hope that wherever you are in your healing journey, you are allowing yourself to grieve and grow and grieve again if you need to. i wish you safe spaces and comfort. i wish you a blade for a tongue. i wish you blocked contacts and safe family gatherings. i wish you brass knuckles. i wish you protection and security. i wish you everything that your precious soul needs and deserves.

text:
on the toughest of days, i try to find my happy place.

cw: assault/abuse #muterkelly

i've had a really tough go today.

i've been taking my time, watching the #survivingrkelly docuseries and i'm trying not to let these experiences break me. as a survivor of sexual and gendered abuse, this sort of thing is so tough to watch but so important.

not only is it hard to watch the survivors telling their stories, it's hard to watch people both in the documentary and real life dismiss, victim blame, centre themselves, and derail the issue.

for everyone: just remember that when you talk about these issues, women are listening. children are listening. survivors are listening. we're hearing what you value, how your opinions are formed, and receiving information on how you will react if we tell you it has happened to us.

for the survivors who are listening... please please please look after yourself. take part in radical self care however you can. find your happy place, your safe space, wherever you feel loved and valued. this is a long battle and you will need to protect your energy.

sending care to all of the folks who are working through their trauma and still trying to fight for justice. i love you. you are valued. you are worthy.

text:
this is a great article about the mental impact of clutter. link in bio! 
i have been working on getting rid of clutter for about 4 years now and have gotten my clothes down to the point where they can all fit into one suitcase. i have lost so much weight i had to buy all new clothes and am being very mindful of what i have been purchasing so everything matches and is high quality. 
in september i put the majority of the items in my house into boxes to see what i really needed in my life and what was just taking up space and have eliminated so many items that were unnecessary.  in my new house i plan to be minimalist and be mindful of the temptation to accumulate possessions and clutter. it's been critical to my sobriety to simplify my life, including my possessions and eliminate. clutter to keep my stress level and anxiety low and make my home a peaceful and calm environment 
two books i read that helped me were the life changing magic of tidying and the gentle art of swedish death cleaning. 
#drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #minimalism #mariekondo #deathcleaning #simplicityeverywhere #soberissexy #soberyogi

text:
the survivor who sent in this story- the seventh submission to the survivor tree project- has a voice that is clear and loud, and transcribing her words brought me so much hope. emily, as she asked to be identified, remembers only bits and pieces of her partially repressed trauma, but what she does recall is compelling: she was attacked by a group of men who cornered her and assaulted her at the age of 13. but the part of emily‚Äôs story that struck me the most was the perspective of gratitude from which she told it. she spoke of how she was able to get herself away before they could ‚Äòdo as much as they potentially wanted.‚Äô she spoke of how the #metoomvmt made her realize how lucky she was. she spoke of how she shared her story with her friends and family and how, with a support system, she learned to handle it. she spoke of how she learned to defend herself and give herself ‚Äòstrength and power to stand above it and not let it keep [her] down‚Äô (emily‚Äôs exact words). üëèüèΩüëèüèΩüëèüèΩ i‚Äôll repeat that again for the people in the back... üó£ strength and power to stand above it and not let it keep her down‚Ä¶ her story is not perfect. she also spoke of how sometimes she feels weak and helpless and still struggles. that‚Äôs okay. healing is not linear and she is not perfect. but her strong is *so much* louder than her weak. ‚Ä¢

emily‚Äôs story is one example of how survivors can face their burdens head on. how they can strengthen themselves and rise higher like a phoenix from the ashes. support and strength and power and confidence like emily‚Äôs are what i hope for for every survivor. emily, i am 100% certain that, in person, you are just as brave and badass as your story is. keep sharing your strength with the world- i‚Äôm so grateful for you! ‚ú®üå± click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute your story to the survivor tree project. #selflove #love #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #thesurvivortreeproject #artist
name: Mel Hanley | Survivor Advocate

text:
3/50  found these gems today. that's my grandmother with my mother. and that is my grandmother with me. it reminds me of the great power of women. it reminds me that we have the death of personality and strengths that is rarely understood and often confused. i know as women that sometimes we forget to honor ourselves as the goddess warrior we are. i also realize that sometimes we forget to recognize other women for the power as well as the great feminine power that it is within ourselves. we are the bearers of children, the nurturers, the disciplinarian, the constant in many people's lives. take a minute today to honor the women in your life and if you are a woman on her the woman within yourself. we rock and we do make this world go round. don't ever forget that. proud warrior goddess love yoursel

text:
can you recognize when you‚Äôre triggered? what is your body telling you?
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
there‚Äôs been a lot of talk around social media in regards to #survivingrkelly. most of the reactions are based on the outrage concerning the singer and the acts of sexual exploitation. but i want to highlight the importance of checking in with self because the information presented in the documentary is very triggering.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
real talk, i had to check in with myself.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
if you‚Äôre starting to feel super uncomfortable, take time to push pause and come back later. give your brain time to process the new information gathered. give your mind time to acknowledge how this may have affected you personally. sometimes it‚Äôs okay to tune out and change the pace. love & hip hop is my guilty pleasure üòå do what works best for you but listen to your mind and body. too much exposure in a short period of time is triggering. and this can definitely lead to symptoms of post traumatic stress disorder, ptsd.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
lastly, reach out. close family and friends may not have the right answers. utilize your community resources and national hotlines. schedule that therapy appointment. this is real life ish and will get to you if you don‚Äôt take care of you.
‚ù§Ô∏è nique
name: Nique Goodman | Teen Therapist

indian womyn did not come to play in 2019. and thank god(dess) for that! our sacred blood makes us holy. the end. 
vermillion goddess red tent stands in proud solidarity with our kerala sisters! 
5.5 million womyn forming a human chain spanning 385 miles. what a divine feminine way to set a precedent! ‚Äúsome hindus believe that menstruation is unclean, and that women should be excluded from daily activities and live in isolation when they have their periods. and some hindu temples bar women from entry while they are on their periods under the belief that their mere presence could ‚Äúdefile‚Äù the religious space. the sabarimala temple took this patriarchal and discriminatory practice even further by barring entry by women of menstruating age altogether.

clearly, women standing up for their bodies and their rights threatens and intimidates many people and institutions everywhere. here in the united states, we must stand in solidarity with the women‚Äôs resistance in kerala. as women around the united states march for our rights later this month, let us remember and express our support of the women‚Äôs wall in kerala. as we build the #metoo movement in the united states, let us also uplift the brave stories of indian women who are speaking up.‚Äù

text:
stay involved saturday!

no other congress has ever looked like this! the 116th congress broke many records including . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . *most number of women ever sworn into congress!
*muslim women serving for the first time!
*native american women are serving for the first time!
*kyrsten sienna not only became the first female senator from arizona, but also makes history as the first openly bisexual senator!
*veronica escobar and sylvia garcia became the first latinas sent to congress by texas!
*the first black congresswoman from massachusetts! *jahana hayes is the first black congresswoman from connecticut! 
many more records have been broken and we are extremely proud!

these newly elected officials will bring important issues to light such as the #metoo movement among other things! we are very excited for the change our new congress members will bring! stay tuned for next weeks ‚Äústay involved saturday‚Äù! #teenswholead #stayinvolvedsaturday *click the link in bio for more information about the topic*

text:
dear @cubagoodingjr, my name is renee and we met at the red lion on christmas day just past midnight. you probably don‚Äôt remember me, you were very drunk. i was so excited to meet you. i‚Äôm a huge fan. i‚Äôve been a fan for at least 22 years. i loved your work. inspirational and moving, like your oscar speech. so when i heard mr. show-me-the-money was in the bar i jumped at the chance to meet you. 
when i found you you were in the back doing a drunken lean on a high top, one foot on the stool rung, trying desperately to look more sober than you clearly were. 20 years of bartending gives you that expertise and insight. ‚Äúmr. gooding i‚Äôm such a huge fan of your work. may i buy you a drink or a shot?‚Äù you looked me up and down with the angry drunk eye and after a while you said, ‚Äúno.‚Äù i understand that most celebrities don‚Äôt want to be bothered. years in the entertainment industry taught me that. i also understand that drunk people sometimes don‚Äôt want to be bothered. again, years in the service industry taught me that. ‚Äúi‚Äôm sorry to bother you. merry christmas.‚Äù and just like that i was going to let it go, no harm no foul. until... ‚Äúyou should‚Äôve offered me sex.‚Äù ‚Äúi‚Äôm sorry?‚Äù i was genuinely stunned and truly thought i‚Äôd misheard you. i searched your face for the joke. found none. instead, you doubled-down. ‚Äúyou should‚Äôve offered sex. or a blow job.‚Äù i don‚Äôt know what kind of stock you think you earn being an oscar-winner but you‚Äôre not allowed to talk to me that way. you are not allowed to talk to women that way. maybe you didn‚Äôt get the memo but #timesup and bad behaviour is no longer excusable no matter how drunk or how famous you are. i never dreamed i‚Äôd have a #metoo moment from someone like you. someone i‚Äôve admired and whose work and talent made me feel safe once upon a time. instead i feel completely violated and absolutely outraged and not posting this would make me a bystander in this day and age. and you should be so lucky anyone wants to buy you a drink and celebrate your life‚Äôs work after making snow dogs. 
so shame on you, cuba. and in the immortal words of @tyrabanks, ‚Äúhow dare you. we were rooting for you.‚Äù sincerely,

text:
recently read an article by the premier of a liberal studies college where they draw parallel between non violence and satyagraha and the losha #metoo movement and coming up with the conclusion that the movement has tremendous potential in addressing oppression.
violence here is presumably treated as a momentary physical act, but is that all that's there to it? missing out on mental and temporal aspects of violence only gives a partial picture of it's impacts. the lopsided justice of metoo gives no opportunity to the alleged to defend themselves, they are not innocent unless proven guilty. under metoo, one starts out with being guilty and it doesn't matter if they are innocent because by the time they prove their innocence, they would already been been sufficiently harassed, shamed and their reputation maligned to ever recover from it. such is metoo's tremendous potential of abuse, a weapon to wreck malicious violence.just how much would this pseudo feminist movement destroy before it realizes that it's on the wrong side of the history!

text:
#metoo: the debacle of countless sexual assaults on western women and islam's solution for it

during the hundreds of years of oppression that the patriarchal western civilization imposed on the female gender and particularly on western women, some movements were launched by women to revive their rights. one of these movements is the #metoo movement which was initially launched by famous western women who had experienced humiliation and sexual harassment. but, will this movement find the cause of this human disaster and the real solution to it?

set your love free
to explore people and get intimidated by them,
give them a thousand reasons to love you amidst the imperfections in this hazy world ,
and if they find something perfect,
let them go!
because when the souls on fire
and everything beautiful,
let them not feel trapped in love,
changed and in charge
to you.
-urmila singh

text_retweet:
repost from @williammichaelbarbee 
i do not get involved in any campaign that brings another human being down. after watching the ‚Äúlifetime‚Äù documentary-series called ‚Äúsurviving r. kelly,‚Äù i can no longer support the brand or music of singer robert sylvester kelly aka. r. kelly. i cried as i listened to all of the survivors‚Äô testimonies about their experiences once they moved in with r. kelly. i cried wondering about the possible experiences that those beautiful children encountered prior to meeting him. my first thought was that we have failed our children. what could possibly separate a child from their parent? it has to be more than just the fascination of an artist. what parent takes a child to a r. kelly concert? we are all culpable in the tragedies of these brown babies. we, as a people have spent a lot of time fighting a system that wrongfully seeks to destroy us as a people. we are often the first criminalized, ridiculed, and demonized. as a result, we tend to overcompensate for those amongst us who do wrong. we forgive the perpetrators and forget the casualties and victims. we must have honest dialogue with ourselves. what have we become? from my platform, this will be the last acknowledgement to anything that is affiliated with r. kelly. i was taught a long time ago, a man who won‚Äôt stand for something, will fall for anything. this is my stance. peace!
#muterkelly @officialmuterkelly #rkelly #mentalillness #sickness #randb #music #metoo @metoomvmt #timesup @timesupnow #blacklivesmatter @blklivesmatter

text:
thank you @lifetimetv for shedding light on the stories of black girls and women.  i watched the entire thing in awe. it was troublesome, but important on so many levels.
-
during this whole new rebirth of the #metoo movement i didn‚Äôt feel like black and brown girls had permission to say, ‚Äúme too‚Äù.
-
@lifetimetv you unmuted our voices with the #survingrkelly docu-series and made me realize two things, one of which i still don‚Äôt have the courage to say aloud, but i have now traced back the roots of some of my own earlier behaviors and i finally realize that my parents or myself were not to blame for somethings that happened to me early in life.
-
i was placing blame for over 30 years, where it did not belong and now i recognize the truth after watching #survivingrkelly
-
secondly, i was able to see the signs of emotional abuse so clearly through #survivingrkelly victims and i always knew that i too had survived emotional abuse on several occasions throughout my life, but it was so much more obvious than it had ever been.
-
this was transformational work and again @lifetimetv, i thank you for shedding light.
-
#blackgirlsmatter #muterkelly #browngirlsmattertoo

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
starting 2019 off with this amazing human was a fantastic moment. ‚ô•Ô∏è this time last year i was still really shaken up by the assault. i wasn't sure how on earth i was ever going to go into london again let alone a date.
i had reached a really dark place again after working so hard to get out of it. having done it once before i knew i could do it again which gave me the strength to go and get the help i needed even though every part of my body was afraid.

being in such a different place know is something i didn't think was even possible. there have been some incredible people who have helped me get through the last year. without them i don't know where i would be. so thank you as you all know who you are.

i have friends who let me call them when i am having a bad day or moment and know exactly how to calm me down. i have colleagues who understand if today is just not my day and i need to go for a walk, go home or even if i can't make it on that day. i have family members who are there for me always no matter what. i have all of you still supporting me by engaging with this page.
and now have the lovely human pictured above who has embraced all of me and made the effort to understand what it is i go through and been there to support me when needed.

i had reached a really dark place again after working so hard to get out of it. having done it once before i knew i could do it again which gave me the strength to go and get the help i needed even though every part of my body was afraid.

being in such a different place know is something i didn't think was even possible. there have been some incredible people who have helped me get through the last year. without them i do not know where i would be. so thank you as you all know who you are.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i‚Äôve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i‚Äôm about to go back, knowing what i know, and we‚Äôre about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump‚Äôs election, trumpeted the return of their ‚Äúpopulist hero‚Äù on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication‚Äôs announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there‚Äôs any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i‚Äôm leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents ‚Äì on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
it is so important to make sure you cleanse yourself and your space of negative, traumatic energy. please take a couple of minutes to take care of yourself before you move onto the next thing. do not allow that energy to stick to you.
if you don't have sage or palo santo or you feel like you don't know how to meditate, just take a quick shower or bathe in some warm water with sea salt or epsom salt and essential oils in it.
i love you.

text:
the #metoo movement has given a voice to so many ladies and girls who have had to endure sexual molestation and harassment from so many powerful men out there. 
the movement has survived and has changed form. 
now, #survivingrkelly has been birthed from the #metoo movement. 
while the stories of these women has and is been told and their courage celebrated, the courage of #johnlegend
should also be told of for standing up for the #meetoo movement. 
and while there are cases like that of #morganfreeman, victims of sexual abuse and assault should be encouraged to tell their stories. 
because the bad guy is black doesn't mean blacks should shy away from speaking up against evil. similarly, if the bad guy is white, people of all colour should shy be bold to speak against this evil. 
#meetoo #survivingrkelly #celebrating_#johnlegend #no_to_sexual_assault

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: i heard news about r kelly child pornography scandal long time ago, but never interested to figure out the case in detail. the documentary series about that was released this week. i think because the momentum was right, with all the #metoo movement and a lot of women have courage to come forward telling their sexual abuse experience. the series interviewed the survivors, ex-wife, family members, friends, co-workers, and some experts. 3 episodes explained about how a talented young man rose to fame, becoming a successful r&b musician and a child predator. behind the sexy and superstar persona, he's a manipulative, unstable, and abusive man. money, biased and double standard that made him untouchable. i hope the survivors are healing and r.kelly will be brought to justice sooner or later. i will never listen to "i believe i can fly" the same way again. #survivingrkelly #rkelly #metoo #biased #doublestandard #childpornography #documentary #sexualabuse #survivors #childpredator

text:
important rant -i haven't seen the new r kelly documentaries, even though i do plan to watch them. the documentary is important not only for exposure but also giving his victims a voice, and encourage others to expose their predators. but right now, all i want is to see that piece of scum in jail. i grew up listening to kelly and when i got older i got into aaliyah (my love) as well. 
their relationship always creeped me out cause i felt the liyah era i liked the most - she was still a teenager, but she was dating kelly who was supposed to be her mentor. only for me to do more reading and see that they married when she was 15. marrying a fifteen year old girl (out of the fear you got her pregnant) that you met and started mentoring when she was 12, being sexual with her, bribing her and her family with $100 not to take legal action... fuck off. people continuously play a part in allowing these predators to succeed in their abuse without any accountability. 
this doesn't start with kelly, or end with kelly. and it doesn't stop in hollywood either. there are girls like liyah everywhere in situations where they're too scared to speak - because even if they do... who will believe them, help them heal, protect and defend them? i'm glad victims of sexual predators are finally speaking out - but the people who knew, and who defend these monsters - they need to be taught accountability too.

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company ‚Äúweaponised‚Äù the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users‚Äô preferences for particular brands on social media platforms ‚Äì facebook, in particular ‚Äì were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign‚Äôs lesser reported ‚Äúweapons of mass destruction‚Äù. - they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone‚Äôs personality. a user‚Äôs predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call ‚Äúpopulist political signalling‚Äù. cambridge analytica, which was¬†shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump‚Äôs former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 ‚Äì including cultural preferences such as fashion and music ‚Äì to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the company‚Äôs problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when you‚Äôre building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a person‚Äôs psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the ‚Äútraining set‚Äù refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your ‚Äúfeature set‚Äù: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, it‚Äôs facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data ‚Äì the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that you‚Äôre trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
~ p r e t e n c e ~
i know i believe in the truth, in seeing something so clearly that you can almost see past it. but sometimes i contradict myself too strongly. i love playing pretend. 
pretending everything is perfect. pretending to be in love. pretending to be perfect. pretending to be revengeful. pretending to be in the present.
pretending to be your long lost soulmate.
pretending to be your man, girl, whatever, when in reality it's just a show i put up. 
i love being the star. 
the stage, all mine. characters, chosen. 
the masks, on. 
and i do understand that i am the one standing alone in the crowd, but it sure makes me feel validated. 
your existence validates me, that's why you exist. sometimes i have venom running in my veins instead of blood, most of the time. but when i think of you, they can see it in my eyes and the audience is keener than ever, waiting for the next twist, watching me toss and turn, in pain. 
and boy, what i great show i put on. 
but that's not who i am, i am a coin, i need both sides for me to be real. i need to be the day and night. poison and antidote. love and hate. reality and a facade. living and dead. 
a little bit of everything, and nothing. 
sincerely than ever,
s

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he‚Äôs the only straight man i‚Äôve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica. - well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage‚Äôs nod to steve bannon certainly hasn‚Äôt aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica‚Äôs influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people‚Äôs personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm‚Äôs vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump‚Äôs campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

females who do the first option are healthier women in general, they are wifey material. the females who jump right into next emotionally or sexually will never grow and never be wife material. they would rather put on a band aid then cure themselves ultimately healing themselves.

females are very easy to read once you understand female nature. as a great pioneer in mgtow once said ‚Äú you can either love women or understand them, but doing both is impossible.‚Äù

text:
there is tremendous power in speaking out and sharing that we faced abuse in childhood or sexual violence when older.

whether that is getting to the stage where we decide to admit it to ourselves and seek counselling or therapy to process it and heal or maybe we seek to disclose formally to the police in order to make a formal statement and seek justice.

in sharing our stories we give other survivors hope, strength and allow other's to see that they are not alone, indeed, if you have never told anyone about your experiences, you are not alone now.

our job now is to shout loudly that it's ok to speak about abuse, it's not shameful, it wasn't our fault, we didnt ask for it and it is not right.

we will shout loudly to other sisters to be their light, guiding them to a sisterhood so that they are no longer alone, but can know that there are other's out here who have lived through dark times but are determined to not allow their past to define their future. 
abuse is not what we are, it is one thing that happened to us.

we are fucking strong.

#speakoutsisterhood
#metoo
#timesup #endviolenceagainstwomenandgirls #itsnosecret #itsnotok #dnalightup
@melcarnegie @sharonabott @womenwithgifts @womensmarch @_thisisnotconsent @thesurvivorstrust @dc_police.999 @sidmouthherald @exeterdailynews @stopchildhoodsexualabusenow

in 2014, steve bannon ‚Äì then executive chairman of the ‚Äúalt-right‚Äù news network breitbart ‚Äì was christopher wylie‚Äôs boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica‚Äôs investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology ‚Äì ‚Äúinformation operations‚Äù ‚Äì then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it‚Äôs insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it‚Äôs like nixon on steroids.

the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn‚Äôs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
project reflecting on a woman's wish to be seen and her simultaneous impulse to hide herself, after centuries of misogynistic programming.

for centuries, women have been reduced solely to their appearance, their physical beauty deemed their only worth. western philosophers who have shaped our collective thinking -¬†aristotle[i], socrates[ii], jean-jacques rousseau[iii], darwin[iv], schopenhauer[v], nietzsche[vi] -¬†compared women to animals, incapable of rational thought, devoid of intelligence. and although present generations are desperately trying to escape these narrow confinements, the ingrained programming leaves many women struggling with their self-worth.

the objectification of the female body is an effective form of dehumanization. women's sexuality is exploited and suppressed at the same time. admired and reviled, chased and judged, praised and ridiculed.¬†this opppresive societal schizophrenia is mirrored in every woman's soul.

this series reflects on the desire to be seen, coupled with the shame and instinctive need to hide.

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn‚Äôs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
i have always found john legend to be a musical genius and love seeing his relationship with his wife and children, but seeing him stand up and speak out against r. kelly and his sickness when no one else in the business who was asked had the same guts to do so, makes me value his character that much more. 
i have said this many times, but why do we continue to support artists who are detrimental to our lives? we continue to support artists who rape our daughters, who believe homosexuals are beneath them, and who continue to degrade us as humans for being different than them. it is time to stand up and make a change. 
i will admit that r. kelly‚Äôs music has been a huge part of my life. his songs make up an enormous part of the soundtrack of my life, but it‚Äôs time we stop creating excuses for those that create good art and think of the humanity of a person.  with that being said, i am standing with the #muterkelly movement and will no longer be playing any of his music. i haven‚Äôt purchased any of his music in years but until watching the documentary never really considered what my continued playing of his music actually represented. 
so from now on when anyone requests an r. kelly song, i will be playing a john legend song instead. stand with me? #muterkelly @johnlegend #protectourdaughters #metoo #enoughisenough #artistsarenotexempt #lawsarelaws #whatsdoneinthedark #thelightiscoming

text:
exactly one year after the first interview of many i finished the documentary. i'm just overwhelmed - one year of work is now pressed in 70 min of moving pictures. 
i'm so glad that i had the opportunity to do everything myself, from creating a concept to directing, filming, interviewing, cutting, producing, writing and recording the music. it was a huge load of work, but i grew with it and so did the project. 
it took a year from this idea of 'let's do a documentary about women in india and see what the outcome is' to a full movie with the title 'women's voice - india's choice'. this actually just makes me so happy. 
thank you all for making this possible. dear strong women of india who let me listen to their stories and feelings, thank you very much!

i'm super excited to share more with you soon.

text:
thank you @kendalljenner for opening up about your struggle with acne. being in an industry that is very self critical and based on beauty it can be devastating when you are feeling less than. i have struggled with acne since my teens and continue to. i have studied and practiced in dermatology and have tried or been on every acne medication on the market. it is a constant battle and i think about my skin every day. throughout my life hormones have taken havoc on my skin. i recently had to take hormones and it triggered horrible cystic acne that i am now managing with multiple medications. talk about work!!! if i am having a bad acne day i admit it affects my mood and how i feel about myself. i have been on the strongest acne medication accutane and developed serious side effects. especially working in my field and being a instagramer i feel i am being judged if i don‚Äôt look perfect. it‚Äôs my job to pick out imperfections! i admit even with consistent effort it may be impossible to completely clear your acne. look at the richest celebrities, they too still have a hard time controlling and treating acne. acne treatment takes consistent daily effort with medication and creams. it‚Äôs exhausting! let‚Äôs remember we are all human and have our struggles. never let that shit stop you- @kendalljennerüíã#metoo #bethechange #shareyourstory tag someone below who struggles with acne. @enews .
.

text:
scriabin sonata 5, opus 53
‚Äî
the fifth sonata, one of the most frequently played of the composer's works, owes a great deal to the orchestral poem of ecstasy, and for this reason the sonata is occasionally given that same title. both draw on a poem by written by¬†scriabin, of which four lines are affixed to the beginning of the sonata (a passage which "calls to life" the artist's "hidden longings," an example of the composer's ever-increasing obsession with his own creative powers), and, while vastly different compositions, both represent the same feverish, concentrated musical world. a deep rumbling from the very bowels of the instrument "calls to life" this restless, 12-minute excursion into the most colorful of passionate realms. delicate, evaporative harmonies built largely of fourths (rather than the more traditional thirds) ensue, wandering about apparently aimlessly but actually working their way to a heated but not violent outburst that does, for a time, seem to be pointing towards an f sharp tonal area. but b major is just as important to the work as its myriad episodes unfold, and the strongest cadential area (implied or otherwise) is the sustained pressure on e flat during the final portion of the piece. just as we feel a final, well-earned resolution coming, however,¬†scriabinthrusts his virtuoso fieldwork up into the stratosphere, where it vanishes without a trace.
.
.
.
.

text:
ptsd...for years i didn't think this applied to me. that nothing in my past was traumatic enough to cause this. i was wrong. for me my brain was busy trying to reconcile what happened and in turn protect itself by downplaying the truth of what happened.  i woke up this morning safe and happy. now i feel lost and almost numb. why? flashbacks. they are nasty little events that bring to the front of my mind what actually happened. it's paralyzing. i had plans for today but can't seem to find the will to do them. 
this is where compassion and love for myself comes in. they are two of my goals. my other unspoken goals is to reach those in need. people like me who are survivors of trauma of any kind. i may be down for now but i will rise again just a little stronger. 
why the gray background? my wish is that when my brain shines a light on the traumas of my past that nothing is there. that it won't need to relive them anymore. but for now i practice self love. i will get up and do my morning routine. complete my habits but my calendar does not need to be full today. today is a day of rest.

#thisisraineysjourney #ptsd #hpxlife #highfunctioningdepression #breakthestigma #metoo #fibromyalgia #survivor #ptsd #pulmonaryembolisurvivor #loveyourself #selfcare #compassion

text:
let me introduce myself. my name is lana - i grew up in a small community with a family about as dysfunctional as any other family. i was the youngest of 4 by 8 years. i was told i was a nice ‚Äúsurprise‚Äù, but my mother had an iud in when she conceived me so i don‚Äôt think surprise is quite the right word üòÇ i was sexually abused and physically beaten by two separate siblings for a long period of my life before the age of 10. the first time i remember a doctor telling me i was morbidly obese, i was 9. i just kept eating. my parents were good people who did the best they could with what they knew, but the emotional trauma i had suffered as a child was never properly dealt with and i continued to eat to bury emotions. by the time i turned 18, i was already at 300lbs. i married my high school sweetheart the and we‚Äôve been together ever since. i never came to terms with my body, and tried loosing weight so many different ways. eventually, i became bulimic. i didn‚Äôt even know a morbidly obese person could be bulimic, but i was. i‚Äôd binge on particularly hard emotional days, and purge after every meal. i lost over 100 lbs twice this way, only to gain it all back. when i reached 339lbs and was told i was pre-diabetic, my heart sank. i had two babies under 10 that i had to make a change for. i underwent vsg surgery july 2015. with that as my tool, i changed every damn habit i had - i busted my ass in the gym, i changed my entire eating habits, and i lost 170lbs. 2 years later i had an abdominoplasty to remove the excess skin from my stomach. about 7 months ago, i had a major mental break down. turns out, 25+ years of emotional trauma that you‚Äôve refused to deal with doesn‚Äôt just disappear. this past year i quit focusing so much on my weight, and focused solely on emotional recovery. i did gain back a little weight during the process, but now am in a place where i can focus my whole attention on a healthy life balance, focusing on the whole me, not just a part of me. ‚ù§Ô∏è

text: there is so much to be learned from this documentary and we can't cover it all in three posts, so we will continue to break it down over the next few days. today however, let's talk about  grooming. r kelly groomed his victims and their families with such precision, which speaks to just how manipulative and calculating these predators are. many of the girls spoke about how he used his charm and sense of humor to put them at ease; how he sought them out on their turf like the mall and school, how he spent time on the phone with them or immediately made them feel special by singling them out and isolating them at parties, and finally how he gradually introduced certain behaviors that were designed to test or eliminate boundaries. all the while, his public behavior, though often vulgar and extremely sexual during performances, was accepted in the name of artistry because of his musical talent and success. therefore, he was able to groom the community into overlooking his rumored and even known behavior leaving so many young girls accessible to him. if parents and the community at large does not begin to understand these patterns of abuse, we can't protect our kids and stop these monsters. i encourage you to go back and listen more intently to the girls' interviews and really dissect how he interacted with them from the moment he met them and then consider how his public persona intersected with how impressionable a teenager or adult might be in the presence of someone with his fame and what they all described as a charming personality. not one of his interactions was without forethought or intent. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #family @officialmuterkelly

text:
#twft52 week 1 - swipe for starter questions and my own response to the prompt (also available via link in profile). ‚úíüñ§
@thewordforthis
***
the word for this is "question.‚Äù
***
"my life‚Äôs sentence, thoughts punctuated and offset within, lived as a curl at the end of certainty; a peak in voice and tone, a breathless view from the top before the sharp drop down and inward, aimed toward some small point within this time i have served."
***
i‚Äôm not the best at simplifying language (understatement). and typically, i choose not to, in this work, in this space. (i‚Äôm bad at twitter. shocking.) when i sat down to address this first prompt, not as leader but as participant, this is what came out. in examining it, connecting it to the past, i saw that what at first felt like commentary on my (over)use of punctuation was in fact a summary of why i write that way to begin with.

the stories of my childhood (too sensitive, both physically and emotionally; my body a currency, a pawn in my ever-fluctuating worth to others, me fully complicit in my devaluing; love and safety and acceptance are conditional, i must earn every moment; not good enough, never good enough) sent me deep inside myself. i‚Äôd have been a writer regardless of the events and dynamics that shaped me. but at any given time, there are four or five fully articulated, parallel thought processes running, and attempting to express in two dimensions becomes absurd. (guess how many documents and browser windows i‚Äôve got open right now? nope, too low. guess again.) so i write the way i think. i write from the place where i feel safest, where i am the enemy i know. the layers of language are self and shield, all at once. and the words? they‚Äôre the cuts i inflict, to heal myself.
***
[please forgive my clumsy tagging; still fighting with the mechanics of all this. imperfect progress. if you'd prefer not to be tagged going forward, just drop a dm to let me know!]

text:
this is a message to @timesupnow and women of color, #metoo and #muterkelly. i have just finished watching surviving r. kelly and i have a few things to say.

first, i want to say that r. kelly is a monster. when they say he is the devil, i believe it. i have never heard of someone who treats women this horribly and degradingly awful. 
second, i want to thank the people who created this series. mute r. kelly has been on a role, but i am fully optimistic that this will benefit all the other women who have been under the same details or in similar incidents. 
third, thank you to the survivors and victims who came forward and participated. i have never seen a group of people with more courage than you. what you did will send shockwaves in the world. and for that, i am grateful. thank you. 
and lastly, i want to say something to the times up. since your creation last year, so many women have come forward to open up about sexual assault and misconduct. i have been a full support since your installation. now with this, i am even more proud to be a supporter. thank you for giving people the courage to come out and say their truths. i wish nothing but the best and i hope to help out one way or another. 
i hope this gives people courage and knowledge that people love and support you no matter what. thank you for reading and keep up the good fight!
#muterkelly #timesup #survivingrkelly #metoo #womenofcolor

text:
finding serenity and calm. my need for solitude and nature is my internal compass and no matter where i end up on this journey, i manage to locate a little haven of peace. it's part of my travel signature. without it, i become lost and completely overwhelmed by the intensity of this journey.‚†Ä
*‚†Ä
there is nothing easy about what i'm doing.  i find myself in dangerous countries where my personal safety is at risk. i face resistance, disbelief and silence. sometimes i have to negotiate hard to talk with people and be heard. in every country i hear stories of horror. i see the extent of sexual abuse and how it is ravaging lives of women, men and children in every corner of the world. the hardest part is confronting the inadequacies of the system, whether it be in the richest country of the world or the poorest, there is so little help available. sometimes i feel completely hopeless but if i find that haven of peace and fill up my cup, everything become possible again. ‚†Ä
*‚†Ä
this incredible garden is in bangkok, thailand. i stumbled upon it by accident escaping a pack of unhappy street dogs. this lush, peaceful garden hidden away far from most tourists routes has been created by a local architect. i spent an entire afternoon here, reading my book, meditating and just being. i had flown in from india the day before and was fried...india tore me to pieces but also gave me so much. a pure paradox and a story for another post. this peaceful afternoon in a secret garden in bangkok and the kindness of my airbnb host restored my hope in humanity and i was ready to face the next leg of the journey. ‚†Ä
*‚†Ä
i ran in thailand on sunday 4 december 2016 - country 10 and only days after the king passed away üñ§

women's only jiu jitsu 
happy 1-year anniversary to our women's only bjj class! from a class that began with just 1 woman, to a class that's grown and evolved into so much more. women, mothers, wives, students.. small, big, tall, short - we welcome all of you - and we welcome more! thank you ladies for an amazing year! we are excited at what's in store for 2019 - which includes an additional class time! women's only brazilian jiu jitsu now offered three times per week: tuesdays/fridays/sundays. come join our family - first class is on the house üòä

first i want to send healing love to all the victims in this documentary and to the abuser. i want to share i will say that i come in love with no judgement but i also stand in healing power for the victims!!! here is what i see!

3.fear-this ugly monster here has control the lives of many and as you can see in this documentary fear is king!! through the victims and the abuser along with the families!! but this is why most victims dont come forth!

6.pedophiles-child abusers but as you can see it 1st starts with being abused!! learned behavior!!

text:
i am not here to debate or argue. i just have one question for the continued supporters, esp. the men. how would you feel if it was your niece, sister, daughter, (grand) daughter, aunt, female cousin involved in this sex ring/cult? 
are we, as society, that "desensitize" to what is going on because the situation has not hit close to home? as a big brother, uncle and godfather to a 12 year old female, this is totally unacceptable. i do not care who you are. 
please stop with the victim shaming! these are women crying out for help telling their story. by discrediting their truth, their testimony, that is the ultimate disrespect. 
also, please, stop with the race issue. no matter who you are, black / white, man / woman, you are a predator/pedophile when you prey on underage teenagers, force them into sexual acts and hold them hostage and keep them away from their loved ones / family. to all of my victims of sexual violence abuse or any type of abuse, that i am seeing on my timeline, we hear you, we see you! speak up and tell your story!! keep in mind, music is the biggest mechanism for brainwashing. #staywoke #muterkelly #timesup #metoo

are we, as society, that "desensitize" to what is going on because the situation has not hit close to home? as a big brother, uncle and godfather to a 12 year old female, this is totally unacceptable. i do not care who you are. 
please stop with the victim shaming! these are women crying out for help telling their story. by discrediting their truth, their testimony, that is the ultimate disrespect. 
also, please, stop with the race issue. no matter who you are, black / white, man / woman, you are a predator/pedophile when you prey on underage teenagers, force them into sexual acts and hold them hostage and keep them away from their loved ones / family. to all of my victims of sexual violence abuse or any type of abuse, that i am seeing on my timeline, we hear you, we see you! speak up and tell your story!! keep in mind, music is the biggest mechanism for brainwashing. #staywoke #muterkelly #timesup #metoo
