text:
#jasminebarns this isn‚Äôt adding up. allegedly this is the driver. they have another man involved with the crime but he hasn‚Äôt been charged yet?  i‚Äôm confused. why show the identity of one and not the other? ‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äîa 20-year-old man in texas was arrested saturday and charged in the death of 7-year-old jazmine barnes, who was shot and killed while riding in a car with her family in houston. another man is being held in connection with the shooting but has not yet been charged, a lawyer for the girl's family said.
~~~
the source provided the sheriff with an instagram account used by one of the suspects, which investigators determined belonged to black, the prosecutor said. on saturday, police stopped black in a grey kia for failing to signal when changing lanes, and held him for suspected marijuana possession after a deputy said he saw a plastic bag in his glove box and searched his car.
~~~
homicide detectives interviewed black on saturday, and the prosecutor said black admitted to driving the vehicle involved in the shooting. black told investigators "lw" was seated in the front passenger seat of a rental car and fired at the car carrying jazmine. black returned that rental car after the shooting and picked up the car he was driving when he was pulled over saturday.
~~~
the prosecutor said in sunday's hearing that black then agreed to a search of his residence, where police found a 9 mm pistol consistent with the gun used in the shooting.
laporsha washington, jazmine's mother, said in the days following the shooting that she believed it was racially motivated. her daughter, who was also in the car, initially said the shooter was a white man in a red truck, and police released an artist's sketch thursday showing a thin, white man with a 5 o'clock shadow. black, the accused driver, is african american.
~~~
investigators plan to hold a news conference sunday afternoon to provide more details on the charges. authorities had offered a $100,000 reward for information leading to an arrest.
~~~

text:
today marks 3 years since making the hardest, most terrifying yet most freeing and best decision of my life. for the first time in my life not only did i find  myself a single mom but the sole provider for not just me but my kids. i stood up to a narcissistic bully. i no longer put up with the abuse he was giving me and our kids and instead i fought for my freedom and to find my self worth. my kids found their worth as well and don't put up with his bullying and manipulation either. 
today, i am beyond happy. life is great. i don't walk on eggshells nor am i afraid to be myself. the single mom life is tough but it is fucking amazing!!!! #lifeafternarcissisticabuse  #lifeafterabuse  #metoo

statistics about sexual assault in the usa: *trigger warning* .
> one in five women will be r*ped at some point in their lives
.
> one in 71 men will be r*ped at some point in their lives
.
> 8 out of 10 r*pe victims will personally know their perpetrator .
> 81% of women, and 35% of men report psychological damage such as ptsd after their assault .
> one in four girls, and one in six boys will be sexually abused before they turn 18 .
> 30% of women were between the ages of 11 and 17 at the time of their first r*pe
.
> 96% of people who sexually abuse children are male
.
> on average 325,000 children per year are at risk of becoming victims of commercial child sexual exploitation .
>over 90% of sexual assault victims of college campuses do not report their assault .
.
these statistics are the product of a r*pe culture that is being continually perpetuated not only in america but around the world. not only do we need to educate our children better, we need to actively speak out against current perpetrators of rape culture. r*pe is not a joke. r*pe is not funny now, nor will it ever be. r*pe doesn‚Äôt happen to people who are ‚Äúasking for it‚Äù. anyone can be a victim of r*pe. anyone can be a victim of r*pe. anyone can be a victim of r*pe. we can no longer turn a blind eye to the suffering being experienced by millions of people around the world. .
.
.
.
if you are a victim of sexual assault,  and feel that you have no one and nothing to turn to you can call the national sexual assault hotline: 1800-656-4673 or you can talk to someone through the online chat. you are not alone, you are stronger than you know, you can make it through this.  #endrapeculture #feminism #metoo

text:
hearing about emotional and physical abuse, i learnt how much people cover up during relationships. george would always assure me everything was okay in a way that i wouldn't step in. now when i feel like there are alarm bells, i will listen to my gut. 
_
it takes a lot of courage to stand up and call someone out on something so life changing, at the time i didn't have the courage to do that. i am learning to find the strength in myself to stand up and say something. when it comes to these situations, you never know if calling someone out could make the situation worse which made me scared to take charge and tell her 'no, this isn't okay.' _
talking about emotional and physical abuse openly needs to start happening more often, so that we can learn about healthy relationships. i think people need reassurance that it will be okay, it will strengthen you to walk away. people say when breakups occur they just need to be alone, but that's when you need to encourage people to speak up and just say truthfully how they feel. living in your head can be a dark place at times, getting it off your chest to someone can help immensely. i know for george, her having space and freedom to talk has helped her heal and grow. it's most certainly taught me a lot. 
@rosiebree 
_
#hearmetoo #metoo #wecandobetter #offmychest #arttherapy #creative #ptsd #emotionalabuse

text:
if this makes you uncomfortable good!
.
.
we want bubbly, pretty and cute to portray our social media feeds most often‚Äî independent of our gender. our desires to fit in with society and identify with our own gender can be a torment. as children we soak in all the information around us, we are exposed to beliefs, peer pressure and the molding of society at hand.  different eras, brought different movements for change to reconcile challenges of inequality‚Äî and still today we battle the human psyche to view each other all as ‚Äòequal beings‚Äô having a human experience.  i believe it is important not to let this social world, especially now that we have it so close to our finger tips, to numb out the relevance and need to hold firm in our beliefs. sticking up for what you believe in is your duty. the masses control consumerism and the notions that are carried forth into action in the world... don‚Äôt forget, that what you watch, how you speak and what you choose to do or not do holds weight and carries a force of approval or disapproval to the outside world. speak up for what you believe in and never stray from your truth, for it is the livelihood of your joy. we teach each other how to treat each other, so hold firmly in your convictions. .
female figures is an art piece created in 2014 by jordan wolfson ‚Äúfor seven minutes the robot gives monologues and dances to pop songs. startling and unnerving, the work raises the specter of misogyny and exposes fissures in pop culture. it challenges the ways women are represented, and the ways images of women are consumed.‚Äù
.

„Éª„Éª„Éª
last year bette midler renewed allegation geraldo rivera groped her... actor posts video of 1991 interview in which she describes alleged assault, saying tv host and producer pushed drugs ‚Äòunder my nose‚Äô

bette midler renewed an allegation of 1970s sexual misconduct against geraldo rivera on thursday, a day after rivera called the news business ‚Äúflirty‚Äù amid matt lauer‚Äôs dismissal by nbc.

in the tweet posted by the actor-singer and confirmed by her publicist, she included a video from the 1991 interview with barbara walters in which midler made the allegation against rivera. ‚Äútomorrow is my birthday. i feel like this video was a gift from the universe to me. geraldo may have apologized for his tweets supporting matt lauer, but he has yet to apologize for this,‚Äù midler posted, adding the harassment-solidarity hashtag ‚Äú#metoo‚Äù. a representative for rivera did not immediately respond to a request for comment. fox news channel, which currently employs rivera but did not in the 70s, did not immediately comment on midler‚Äôs post.

in the clip, midler hesitates in recounting what she alleges happened with rivera during his visit to interview her in the early 70s, saying it will get her in trouble. ‚Äúget in a little trouble,‚Äù walters encourages her.

after rivera and a producer left their tv crew in another room, they ‚Äúpushed me into my bathroom. they broke two poppers and pushed them under my nose and proceeded to grope me,‚Äù she said. ‚Äúpoppers‚Äù is slang for the alkyl nitrites class of drugs. ‚Äúi did not offer myself up on the altar of geraldo rivera,‚Äù said midler, calling his behavior ‚Äúunseemly‚Äù. after midler tells walters that she had no way of knowing ‚Äúthese things are going to come back to haunt you‚Äù, walters suggests they discuss other subjects.
#survivingrkelly #rkelly --------------------------------------------------

text:
debut novel by lily jane bell,
slap ‚Äòn‚Äô tickle - the first abuser was lovely...
let‚Äôs talk genres. back in the day i tried the conventional route of publishing, i consistently hit a brick wall - my book was incredibly well received, lots of fantastic critiques but i was repeatedly told that i didn‚Äôt fit any one genre. now, i know my writing isn‚Äôt conventional, (neither am i) but i plain refused to give up. recently, i was paid a wonderful compliment by an unknown purchaser of slap ‚Äòn‚Äô tickle. they drew comparisons to the style of writing in the number one bestseller ‚Äòeleanor oliphant is completely fine‚Äô by gail honeyman. after reading the book (beautifully written) i was stunned to read what was indeed a close representation of my style and content. that said, it doesn‚Äôt have as many expletives as slap ‚Äòn‚Äô tickle! food for thought...perhaps when the proverbial round peg doesn‚Äôt fill a hole we don‚Äôt give up, we think laterally and take a sneaky way round the problem. after all, who wants to be a round peg anyway? 
#bookstagram #mentalhealthawareness #metoo #gailhoneyman

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
"una sombra desde la ventana dijo: "para evitar al lobo deber√°s tener suerte cada vez... pero al lobo... al lobo le basta con tener suerte una vez".
.
üìö
hace poco relee√≠ cruzando el bosque de emily carroll, una colecci√≥n de cuentos con toque siniestro, donde las protagonistas, mayoritariamente mujeres deben enfrentarse a los peligros que acechan camuflados entre las personas de su d√≠a a d√≠a. cuando lo le√≠ la primera vez me gust√≥, pero esta segunda vez, tal vez influenciada por el movimiento #metoo, por todas las conversaciones que hemos tenido este a√±o como sociedad sobre consentimiento y que significa ser una mujer en una sociedad machista, los monstruos de carroll se me han hecho mucho m√°s reales que la √∫ltima vez.
.
üìö
precisamente, la primera foto, que es la √∫ltima p√°gina de la colecci√≥n, me parece que resume muy bien el problema de las mujeres y el espacio p√∫blico. no importa cuantas veces llegues sana y salva a casa, como la protagonista de la historia, el lobo solo tiene que cazarte una vez para cambiar el desenlace para siempre. lo peor, es que el lobo, como los monstruos en las historias de caroll no siempre tienen una imagen aterradora.
.
üìö
pero m√°s all√° de mis interpretaciones, no se puede negar que cruzando el bosque es una colecci√≥n bastante potente de cuentos, d√≥nde la tensi√≥n se transmite no solo a trav√©s de la historia, sino de los dibujos de la propia carroll que juegan muy bien con los espacios, las ausencias y los colores. esta colecci√≥n de 5 cuentos es ideal tanto para los amantes de los cuentos tradicionales (de los que las historias y la est√©tica de carroll se alimentan) como para los amantes del suspense (que llena las p√°ginas), o simplemente para aquellos que quieran pasar un buen rato con historias que sin ser nada nuevo aportan una vuelta de tuerca interesante. .
üìö

text:
#24speciesofcrane day 25

balearica pavonina, the black crowned crane.

this beautiful bird sports a very long neck topped with a tuft of yellow hair and a bright red patch of bare skin, and is considered to closely resemble the prehistoric ancestors of modern day cranes. while the specimen photographed was spotted in the most beautiful wine country in the world, it has been considered #extinct in the entire universe outside sub-saharan africa. habitat destruction must stop to save this bird. 
this birds diet consists of reptiles and small mammals and birds. it is suspected that the quails native to this area attracted the bird in for a delicious meal, perhaps kicking off with local vegan clams followed by the deliciously #vegan cornish game hen with crispy skin and a rich sauce. likely ending with some grapefruit and lychee sorbet for a clean palate to enjoy the foch or optima dessert wines.

text:
kogan maintains that everything he did was legal and he had a ‚Äúclose working relationship‚Äù with facebook, which had granted him permission for his apps.

cambridge analytica had its data. this was the foundation of everything it did next ‚Äì how it extracted psychological insights from the ‚Äúseeders‚Äù and then built an algorithm to profile millions more.

for more than a year, the reporting around what cambridge analytica did or didn‚Äôt do for trump has revolved around the question of ‚Äúpsychographics‚Äù, but wylie points out: ‚Äúeverything was built on the back of that data. the models, the algorithm. everything. why wouldn‚Äôt you use it in your biggest campaign ever?‚Äù in december 2015, the guardian‚Äôs harry davies published the first report about cambridge analytica acquiring facebook data and using it to support ted cruz in his campaign to be the us republican candidate. but it wasn‚Äôt until many months later that facebook took action. and then, all they did was write a letter. in august 2016, shortly before the us election, and two years after the breach took place, facebook‚Äôs lawyers wrote to wylie, who left cambridge analytica in 2014, and told him the data had been illicitly obtained and that ‚Äúgsr was not authorised to share or sell it‚Äù. they said it must be deleted immediately.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
thank you to everyone for your lovely messages & stories shared with me over the past few days. 
your kindness has honestly given me so much hope. -
while wednesday was horrible, it has since left me with nothing but ideas & plans for better care. 
hearing so many of your similar stories honestly breaks my heart & makes my blood boil & i‚Äôm hoping to put some of my plans & ideas into place soon so stay postedüå∏
-
i, like so many other of yous i‚Äôm sure feel incredibly let down, alone and uncared for by the system. but remember that this isn‚Äôt true. yes we have been let down but that doesn‚Äôt take away from you being incredibly cared for and just because they can‚Äôt provide you help and support doesn‚Äôt mean you don‚Äôt deserve it. i‚Äôm now in the process of finding my own supports. non governmental organisations seem to be the way to go. -
to everyone struggling remember why you have hung on for so long. 
you deserve to be happy & peaceful & know that it‚Äôs okay to need help üíú

text: so, when i was in la recently, bored af, i decided to go on a solo mission to a top club there.minding my business in the corner sipping my pineapple juice just observing the usual vip fronting popping bottles, two sets of ladies approached me.1 very attractive lady in particular walked up to me & asks where my girlfriend was..huh? i don‚Äôt have one, next thing she grabs deez nutz & starts molesting me! üòÜ i‚Äôd never been fingered before.. yooo! in my head i‚Äôm thinking call girl but then again she was tipsy! so we chatted & at the end, to her amazement i don‚Äôt ask her to go home. she asked for my number, next day she hits me up like wow, u really different.. can i buy lunch & show u around la? i was like, sure. man by the time this girl told me her story while balling in tears, i was not only angry but traumatized b! at age 4, uncle had molested her! by 9 her biological father was having sex with her! by 11, her mums brother & dad ran train on her, by 14 her mum was pimping her to raise money for her drug habits, by 17 her white boyfriend was pimping her to strip clubs! by the time she broke down how most sex industry girls get to being where they are.brah, i had a headache! in the greatest country in the world! this girl literally didn‚Äôt know she had options / choices! by the time she was asking me if atlanta would be the same, i was like sweetheart, you can go to torrence and it would be different! it was surreal as if i‚Äôd met a wolf from the jungle! i was like yeah i need to do a major healing tour. in my head i‚Äôm like if this is happening in america, can you imagine what our little sisters go through in 3rd world?! y‚Äôall men need to stop this sh!t for real! you out here destroying these little girls & wonder y they‚Äôre so angry! uncles turning out these lil boys then telling them they were born that way üò°!these kids are lost, talk to these people like humans and you won‚Äôt believe what you learn! stop demonizing all of them these behaviors are not normal but they don‚Äôt know better.their parents didn‚Äôt protect /village failed them! i think early adoptions should be mandatory if there‚Äôs severe cases of mental health!cz soon they‚Äôll be parents #muterkelly #metoo
